Something sad and terrible is happening to the Netherlands, long one of Europe's tolerant, decent and multicultural societies.
The Dutch government has declared war on Islamic extremism following the brutal killing of filmmaker and columnist Theo van Gogh by a suspected radical Muslim, which brought the threat of Islamic violence to home.
The arrest of an alleged Islamic extremist in the slaying of filmmaker Theo van Gogh prompted a conservative Dutch political leader to suggest that Islamic radicals suspected of crimes be deported.
